<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>I noticed an error while using the form view helpers -- the method <em>_loadClass</em> in Zend_View_Abstract has this code:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
if (isset($this-&gt;$classLoaded[$name])) {
    return $this-&gt;$classLoaded[$name];
}
</code></pre>

<p>Due to the operator priorities, the <em>isset</em> is always returning true. I had to resolve the ambiguity by writing:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
if (isset($this-&gt;{$classLoaded}[$name])) {
    return $this-&gt;{$classLoaded}[$name];
}
</code></pre>

    </div>
</div>

